# ☕ Coffee Machine Project

A simple **Python-based Coffee Machine simulation** that lets users order espresso, latte, or cappuccino.  
The program checks ingredient availability, processes payments with virtual coins, returns change, and updates remaining resources — just like a real coffee machine!
---

## 🧠 Project Overview
This project is part of the **100 Days of Code – Python** challenge.  
It was built to practice:
- Functions and loops  
- Conditional statements  
- Dictionaries and nested data structures  
- Resource management and logic flow
---

## 🚀 Features
✅ Menu options: **Espresso, Latte, Cappuccino**  
✅ Resource check (water, milk, coffee)  
✅ Coin-based payment system (quarters, dimes, nickels, pennies)  
✅ Automatic change calculation  
✅ Dynamic inventory updates  
✅ “Report” command to view current resources  
✅ “Off” command to stop the machine  
---

